headline: CrowdStrike (CRWD) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of cybersecurity platform provider CrowdStrike (NASDAQ:CRWD) jumped 3% in the morning session after momentum in the SaaS segment improved, supported by reports that the company entered into a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Aramco to advance Saudi Arabia's cybersecurity transformation.

headline: 3 SaaS Stocks Worth Buying Despite The Meltdown
summary: The Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) sector has dropped 30% in the last 90 days and is still gushing blood.
